column3: Celery is rich in vitamins and minerals with a low glycemic index, which means it has a slow and steady effect on blood sugar. It's also rich with vitamins A, K, and C, plus minerals like potassium and folate.
Cucumbers are packed with vitamin K, B and C along with minerals like copper, phosphorus, potassium and magnesium.
column4: Raw, Salads, Smoothies, Roll Ups, Dips, Dressings, Toppings, Garnish

column3: Green beans are a great source of minerals, especially manganese. This cool mineral helps support metabolism, plus it has antioxidant abilities, and supports bone health and wound healing.
column4: Roasted, Pickled, Marinated, Grilled, Fried, Braised, Salads

column3: Green cabbage is exceptionally healthy with high levels of vitamins C and K. It may help lower your risk of certain diseases, and can help with digestion and inflammation.
Green onions are a great source of vitamin K, C and A.
column4: Topping, Stir Fy, Salads, Sandwiches, Pancakes, Baking, Sauces
